Express is a backend of the mean stack. It uses javascript for the backend, which is rare because most other stacks use javascript for frontend. The mean stack uses javascript for the frontend and the backend of web development. Express can be described as middleware or what is between the server and the client. Express is easy to test as well, because it is between the two. Express has a wide range of functions. It has successfully used the NPM. So, people can customize express based on what third party plugins they choose. Since express is built on top of node.js, it is faster. Express has a lot of community support for it because it handles things like cookies, routes, and requesting body and forming the response. And it is usually better for small to medium projects. Overall, express is a minimal bundle of features and functions that make it easier to build web apps.
